Aloha President Kouchi, Speaker Nakamura, Members of the Legislature, and Revisor of
Statutes:
Pursuant to Section 9 of Act 218, Session Laws of Hawai'i 2023, I hereby notify the Legislature
and the Revisor of Statutes that the transfer of all properties authorized to be acquired by Act
218 were recorded with the Bureau of Conveyances on June 22, 2026.
Act 218 authorized the acquisition of the Wahiawa Irrigation System and associated
improvements by the Department of Agriculture and Biosecurity, Department of Land and
Natural Resources, and Agribusiness Development Corporation. The conveyances authorized
by the Act have been completed and recorded in accordance with the requirements of Sections
3 and 9 of Act 218.
The successful completion of these transfers preserves a critical agricultural and water
infrastructure asset for the State of Hawai'i and ensures the continued public benefits associated
with the Wahiawa Irrigation System.

Accordingly, the condition set forth in Section 9 of Act 218 has been satisfied.
